    "content": "Under Graduate Courses (B.Tech) - B. P. Poddar Institute of Management & Technology Skip to content 98364 36999 B. P. Poddar Institute of Management & Technology Approved by AICTE, New Delhi & Affiliated to MAKAUT, W.B Home › Admission › Under Graduate Courses (B.Tech) Under Graduate Courses (B.Tech) Share on Facebook Share on X (Twitter) Share on Whatsapp Share on Telegram Share on Email Under Graduate Programs B.Tech Courses Offered at BPPIMT Sr. No Program Total Intake 1 B.Tech in Computer Science & Engineering (NBA accredited) 180 2 B.Tech in Electronics and Communication Engineering (NBA accredited) 60 3 B.Tech in Electrical Engineering (NBA accredited) 30 4 B.Tech in Information Technology (NBA accredited) 120 5 B.Tech in Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning 60 Eligibility for B.Tech at BPPIMT H.S (10+2) Examination of the Council of Higher Secondary Education, West Bengal or equivalent with Physics and Mathematics along with any one of Chemistry / Biotechnology / Biology / Computer Science / Computer Application/ Technical Vocational Subject as compulsory subjects with individual pass marks (in both theory and practical wherever applicable) in all the three subjects as stated above in regular class mode. At least 30% marks in English and minimum 45% marks in the above three subjects taken together. Qualified Joint Entrance Examination conducted by West Bengal Joint Entrance Examinations Board, JEE (Main) conducted by NTA and recommended by the WBJEE Board. The Board of the said Qualifying Examination must be recognized by the Central Government or State Government concerned. Brochure & Leaflet Fee Structure for B.Tech at BPPIMT Category Amount Admission Fee (one time) 10,000 Tuition Fee 60,500 Development Fee 9,075 Library & Book Bank Fee (one time) 6,000 Students welfare, Sports & Games fee (one time) 4,000 Caution Deposit (one time) (To be refunded on completion of full tenure of the course) 10,000 Admission Kit (non-refundable) 1,000 At the time of Admission 1,00,575 Fee for Each (2nd to 8th Semester) Category Amount Tuition Fee 60,500 Development Fee 9,075 Total Amount Payable 69,575 University Development & Registration Fee (one time) (To be paid at the time of Registration) Subject to change as per MAKAUT norms 2,700 The total amount to be paid by Demand Draft/Pay Order (MICR only) in favour of “B.P.PODDAR INSTITUTE OF MANAGEMENT AND TECHNOLOGY” Payable at Kolkata or Online Payment through Net Banking, NEFT etc. As per Ref. No: 466-Edn-(T)/l0M -04/2004 (Part IV) Dated: 16.10.2023 N.B.: Fees once paid shall not be refunded under any circumstances. Documents Required at the Time of Admission for B.Tech at BPPIMT (WITH SELF ATTESTED AND DATE OF ALL DOCUMENTS) Three (03) sets attested photocopies of Marksheets of class X, XII Three (03) sets attested photocopies of Admit Card of Class X / Birth Certificate Two (02) Recent Coloured Passport size photographs. Three (03) downloaded copies of Rank Card. Two(02) photocopies of final Allotment. Three (03) photocopies of Aadhaar Card. Two(02) photocopies of Domicile Certificate (Link: https:// wbjeeb.in/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Information-Bulletin-WBJEE-2024-Final211223-7-50PM.pdf )) Two(02) photocopies of Caste Certificate (as applicable) should be submitted at the time of admission Two (02) Photocopies of Income Certificate (applicable for TFW Candidate only) Two (02) Photocopies of EWS Certificate (applicable for EWS allotted candidate only) Medical and Eye Specialist Certificate (in the prescribed forms of the college). All original testimonials to be produced at the time of admission No Provision for admission under any Reserved Category Quota viz SC,ST, OBC, Minority and PwD candidate. Uniform is mandatory (Available from Institute recommended Dressmaker) B.Tech (Lateral Entry)- 3 years Important Dates for JELET 2025 Information Bulletin Published – 2nd September 2025 (Tuesday) Online application with payment of fees – 9th September 2025 (Tuesday) to 17th September 2025 (Wednesday) Online correction and downloading revised confirmation page – 1 9th September 2025 (Friday) to 20th September 2025 (Saturday) Publication of Downloadable Admit Card – 1 0th October 2025 (Friday) to 18th October 2025 (Saturday) Date of Examination – 1 8th October 2025 (Saturday) (11:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m.) Apply Online for JELET 2025 Eligibility Criteria for Admission via JELET Qualified JELET conducted by West Bengal Joint Entrance Examinations Board. Diploma holders seeking admission into Engineering & Technology Degree Courses: The candidate must pass Diploma in ANY branch from an institute approved by AICTE for admission in ANY branch of Engineering & Technology. The candidate must secure at least 45% (40% for SC/ ST/ OBC-A/ OBC-B/ PwD) marks or equivalent CGPA in diploma examination. B. Sc. candidates seeking admission into Engineering & Technology Degree Course: The candidate must pass B. Sc. Degree from any University recognized by UGC with at least 45% (40% for SC/ ST/ OBC-A/ OBC-B/ PwD) marks Also, the candidate must have passed 12 th standard school examination with Mathematics as a subject. The candidate, if admitted, will have to clear the subjects of Engineering Mechanics and Engineering Graphics / Engineering Drawing of the 1st year Degree Course in Engineering/Technology along with their second-year subjects. Fee Structure for 2nd year B.Tech (Lateral Entry) Students 2025-26 Category Amount Admission Fee (one time) 10,000 Tuition Fee 60,500 Development Fee 9,075 Library & Book Bank Fee (one time) 6,000 Students welfare, Sports & Games fee (one time) 3,000 Caution Deposit (one time) (To be refunded on completion of full tenure of the course) 10,000 Admission Kit (non-refundable) 1,000 At the time of Admission 99,575 Fee for Each (4 th to 8 th semester) Category Amount Tuition Fee 60,500 Development Fee 9,075 Total Amount Payable 69,575 University Development & Registration Fee (one time) (To be paid at the time of Registration) Subject to change as per MAKAUT norms 2,700 As per Ref. No: 466-Edn-(T)/l0M -04/2004 (Part IV) Dated: 16.10.2023 N.B.: Fees once paid shall not be refunded under any circumstances. Documents Required at the Time of Admission (WITH SELF ATTESTED AND DATE OF ALL DOCUMENTS) Three (03) sets attested photocopies of Marksheets of class X, XII & Diploma course (all Semesters) Three(03) sets attested photocopies of Admit Card of Class X Two (02) Recent Coloured Passport size photographs. Three (03) downloaded copies of Rank Card. Three (03) photocopies of Aadhaar Card. Two (02)Photocopies of Domicile Certifiate (Link: https:// wbjeeb.in/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2024020274-jelet-2024.pdf ) Two (02) Photocopies of Caste Certificate (as applicable) Two (02) Photocopies of final Allotment. All original testimonials to be produced at the time of admission No Provision for admission under any Reserved Category Quota viz SC,ST, OBC, Minority and PwD candidate. Uniform is mandatory (Available from Institute recommended Dressmaker) Lateral Entry to second year B.Tech shall be permissible up to a maximum of 10% of the “approved intake” which shall be over and above, supernumerary to the “approved intake” plus unfilled vacancies of the first year. Contact our city office for admission related queries B.P.Poddar Institute of Management and Technology 87, Park Street (Opp St. Xavier’s College, Beside Park Street Police Station) Kolkata – 700016 91-033-2265 7150 91-033-2265 7152 +91 98364 36999 [email protected] Mr. Santanu Banerjee Related Pages Admission Post Graduate Course (M.Tech) Post Graduate Course (MCA) Under Graduate Courses (B.Tech) Under Graduate Courses (BBA, BCA) Scholarship Schemes Quick Links Affiliating University NIRF NBA Mandatory Disclosure Archive New sletters Events Achievements Media Coverage Human Resources Board of Governors Administration Academic Advisory Body Technical Staff Forum & Cell Internal Quality Assurance Cell Internal Complaint Committe