  {
    "id": "web-14",
    "title": "Central Library",
    "url": "https://bppimt.ac.in/institute-cells/central-library/",
    "content": "Central Library - B. P. Poddar Institute of Management & Technology Skip to content 98364 36999 B. P. Poddar Institute of Management & Technology Approved by AICTE, New Delhi & Affiliated to MAKAUT, W.B Home › Institute Cells › Central Library Central Library Share on Facebook Share on X (Twitter) Share on Whatsapp Share on Telegram Share on Email The library plays a key role in the academic activities of the Institute. It is conveniently located in a spacious accommodation with Open Access facility for providing support to large number of students. The library has a large collection of Books and Print Journals. Stock of books is regularly updated with the latest editions. The Institute has a Digital Library that enables students to access E-Resources. The Institute subscribes two categories of E-journals – Springer and J-Gate, by which various International Journals can be accessed and downloaded. In addition to automated search and issue of books, the book bank facility is also provided to students to maintain quality learning. Multimedia facility is available to encourage the students for e-learning. The library has Springer e-books with perpetual license of more than 2800 titles available to the students through digital library to enhance the quality of learning experience. The library is also equipped with a set of National Program on Technology Enhanced Learning (NPTEL) recommended lecture videos. The library has subscription of DELNET & membership of NDL. Please follow the link provided for guidelines on accessing E-resources remotely : E-Resources Function of the Cell To collect, organize and disseminate print and electronic information to the Faculties and the Students of the Institution. To enhance and support the research activity of the Institution and to act as Learning Resource Centre. To plan and implement routine activities of the Library To work towards modernization and improvement of Library To formulate policies and procedures for efficient use of Library resources To approve requisition for new books / journals in accordance with the requirements. To prepare budgetary requirements To seek feedback on Library functions from readers To maintain library discipline and promotes library usage Facilities of the Cell Library lending room for issuing and returning of books. Air-conditioned Reading room with Open access facility with approximately 120 seating capacity. Digital library, Multimedia and Journal room containing 30 PCs for accessing e-resources with approximately 50 seating capacity. Photocopying room with photocopy facility. Book Bank Facility by giving 5–6 text books to the Students according to their curriculum for a whole academic semester. Apart from the Book bank facility, all the Students can issue another 3 books per semester. Computerized system for searching for the books available in the Library. Computerized issue/return facility with bar code scanning. Provision for e-learning system like – Springer e-books, DELNET, NPTEL, NDL Provision for e-journals facility like – Springer, J-Gate. All the e-resources can be accessed remotely 24 x 7 Roles & Responsibilities Coordinator: Plans and coordinates the Library cell’s work. Conducts meetings and keeps committee members fully informed. Prepares budget in consultation with the Librarian and other Faculty members of the committee. Faculty Members: Attend the meetings of the committee. Coordinates with the departments regarding library books/journals requisition. Interact with the departmental student members for library related issues. Student Members: Attend the meetings Coordinates with the Students and takes feedback regarding the library. Inform the departmental Faculty members if any library related issue arises. Librarian Maintains records regarding the titles/volumes of books/journals available Prepares budgetary requirements and expenditure statements/records. Maintains the usage registers. Committee Composition Coordinator: One Senior Faculty member from CSE department Faculty members: One Faculty member from each department (CSE, ECE, IT, EE, MCA) and two Faculty members from Bas. Sc. & Hu Librarian: The Librarian Library Assistant: One Library Assistant Students members: One student member per year from each department (CSE, ECE, IT, EE, MCA & M.Tech (DS)) Committee Members Faculty Members Sl. No. Name Designation Role 1 Mr. Subhasis Mallick AP, CSE Member 2 Ms. Madhumita Mondal AP, EE Member 3 Dr. Madhumita Sarkar AP, ECE Member 4 Mr. Balaram Ghosal AP, IT Member 5 Ms. Pampa Ghosh Saha AP, MCA Member 6 Dr. Rupa Paul AsP, ASH Member 7 Dr. Papri Saha AsP, ASH Member 8 Mr. Pallab Kumar Bhoumik Dy. Lib Member 9 Mr. Soumendra Mukherjee Lib. Asst. Member 10 Mr. Amlan Raychaudhuri AP, CSE Coordinator Student Members Sl. No. Stream Name Year Section 1 CSE Advaita Chatterjee 4th B 2 CSE Tannistha Ghosh 3rd C 3 CSE Souvik Karmakar 2nd B 4 CSE Sushrita Pal 1st B 5 ECE Gairik Banerjee 4th A 6 ECE Mamuni Gupta 3rd A 7 ECE Anshuman Guha 2nd A 8 ECE Saptadwipa Bhattacharjee 1st D 9 IT Ambapali Datta 4th — 10 IT Dipanwita Chatterjee 3rd A 11 IT Aritro Paul 2nd A 12 IT Ritam Dutta 1st C 13 EE Nandan Dutta 4th — 14 EE Arpan Pal 3rd — 15 EE Joy Chakrabarty 2nd — 16 EE Sagnik Dutta 1st D 17 MCA Nausheen Qaiyum 2nd — 18 M.Tech (DS) Kamal Kumar Das 2nd — Timings Tuesday to Saturday 9.00 A.M to 7.30 P.M On working days the services of different sections of the Library remains open as per the following schedule Digital Library / Reference Section 9.00 am to 7.30 pm Lending Section 9.00am to 6.00pm Photo copying Service 9.00am to 6.00pm Library Collections Book Titles : 2833 Book Volumes : 48557 E-BOOKS : 4175 E-JOURNALS : SPRINGER, J-GATE NO OF PRINT JOURNALS : 60 LIST OF SUBSCRIPTION : E-JOURNALS – SPRINGER, J-GATE E -BOOKS – SPRINGER. & DELNET. OTHERS : NDL (MEMBER), NPTEL (LOCAL CHAPTER) Print Journal E-Resources News Paper ACADEMIC YEAR 2024-2025 Sr No Journal Name 1 Advancement of Computer Technology