ostel students. To monitor the security of students. To monitor the basic facilities provided by the Hostel Management time to time. To monitor and inspect the cleanliness in hostel. To conduct surprise visit to the hostel to check quality of services provided. To interact with students from the hostel on a regular basis. Roles & Responsibilities of the Mentors: To monitor the Cleanliness & Hygiene regularly To monitor the Food quality and Service regularly To monitor the Basic facilities of the hostel regularly To report the committee the issues related to any of the above Committee Composition Co-ordinator of the Committee The composition of committee comprises of one senior faculty member as coordinator from Department of Applied Sciences and Humanities. Boy’s Hostel Members One Faculty member each from Department of Information Technology & Applied Science & Humanities One Technical Assistant member each from Department of Applied Sciences & Humanities and Electrical Engineering. One member from Administration Girl’s Hostel Members One Faculty member each from Department of Electrical Engineering, Electronics and Communication Engineering and Computer Science Engineering. Two Technical Assistant members from Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering and Master of Computer Application. Student Committee Member Boys Hostel – Three students from First year, Two students from second and fourth year, four students from third year. Girls Hostel – Four third and fourth year students, two second year and three first year students. Committee Members Sl. No. Name Designation Role 1. Dr. K. Prabakaran Assistant Professor, Bas. Sc. & Hu. Coordinator 2. Ms. Sujatha Saha Assistant Professor, EE Member 3. Ms. Banhi Das Assistant Professor, ECE Member 4. Ms. Piu Upadhyay Assistant Professor, CSE Member 5. Ms. Bhaswati Sadhukhan Technical Assistant, ECE Member 6. Ms. Sudeshna Roy Technical Assistant, MCA Member 7. Mr. Sabyasachi Chakraborty Assistant professor, IT 